// ==================== SETUP INSTRUCTIONS ====================

/**
 * üéÆ OTO TOURNAMENT BOT - COMPLETE SETUP GUIDE
 * ============================================
 * 
 * STEP 1: FILE STRUCTURE
 * ----------------------
 * Create this folder structure:
 * 
 * oto-tournament-bot/
 * ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.js          (Main file - Copy ALL 3 artifact parts here)
 * ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ package.json      (This file)
 * ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .env             (Environment variables)
 * ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ .gitignore
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 2: COMBINE ALL CODE
 * ------------------------
 * In index.js, combine all 3 artifact parts in this order:
 * 
 * 1. Start with "OTO Bot - Complete System" (Part 1)
 *    - Contains: Config, DataManager, Profile System, Greetings
 * 
 * 2. Add "OTO Bot - Part 2" (Payment & Tournament Management)
 *    - Contains: Payment approval, Tournament start, Leaderboards
 *    - REMOVE the duplicate client.on() declarations at the start
 * 
 * 3. Add "OTO Bot - Part 3" (Support, Staff Tools & Startup)
 *    - Contains: Support tickets, Staff commands, Bot ready event
 *    - REMOVE any duplicate functions
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 3: ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (.env file)
 * -----------------------------------------
 * Create .env file with:
 * 
 * BOT_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token_here
 * OWNER_ID=your_discord_user_id_here
 * PORT=3000
 * NODE_ENV=production
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 4: .gitignore FILE
 * -----------------------
 * Create .gitignore with:
 * 
 * node_modules/
 * .env
 * *.log
 * .DS_Store
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 5: INSTALL DEPENDENCIES
 * ----------------------------
 * Run in terminal:
 * 
 * npm install
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 6: DISCORD BOT SETUP
 * -------------------------
 * 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
 * 2. Create New Application
 * 3. Go to "Bot" section
 * 4. Click "Add Bot"
 * 5. Enable these Privileged Gateway Intents:
 *    ‚úÖ PRESENCE INTENT
 *    ‚úÖ SERVER MEMBERS INTENT
 *    ‚úÖ MESSAGE CONTENT INTENT
 * 
 * 6. Copy bot token to .env file
 * 
 * 7. Go to OAuth2 ‚Üí URL Generator
 * 8. Select scopes:
 *    ‚úÖ bot
 *    ‚úÖ applications.commands
 * 
 * 9. Select bot permissions:
 *    ‚úÖ Administrator (or specific permissions)
 * 
 * 10. Use generated URL to invite bot to server
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 7: CHANNEL & ROLE IDS
 * --------------------------
 * Update CONFIG in index.js with your channel IDs:
 * 
 * How to get IDs:
 * 1. Enable Developer Mode in Discord (Settings ‚Üí Advanced)
 * 2. Right-click channel/role ‚Üí Copy ID
 * 3. Paste in CONFIG object
 * 
 * Required Channels:
 * - ANNOUNCEMENT_CHANNEL
 * - TOURNAMENT_SCHEDULE
 * - HOW_TO_JOIN
 * - GENERAL_CHAT
 * - STAFF_TOOLS
 * - STAFF_CHAT
 * - INVITE_TRACKER
 * - LEADERBOARD_CHANNEL
 * - PROFILE_CHANNEL
 * - MINECRAFT_CHANNEL (optional)
 * 
 * Required Roles:
 * - STAFF_ROLE
 * - ADMIN_ROLE
 * - PLAYER_ROLE
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 8: RUN THE BOT
 * -------------------
 * npm start
 * 
 * For development with auto-restart:
 * npm run dev
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 9: TEST ALL FEATURES
 * -------------------------
 * 
 * ‚úÖ User Features:
 * - Join server ‚Üí Check DM for profile setup
 * - Complete profile
 * - Type -i (check invites)
 * - Type -profile (view profile)
 * - Type -help (bot help)
 * - Say "Hi" in general (auto-response)
 * - Mention bot (quick help)
 * 
 * ‚úÖ Tournament Features:
 * - Staff: !ct (create tournament)
 * - Select template from dropdown
 * - Publish tournament
 * - User: Join tournament
 * - Staff: !startroom <id> <roomID> <password>
 * - Staff: !winners <id> @user1 @user2 @user3
 * - Staff: !endtournament <id>
 * 
 * ‚úÖ Support System:
 * - User: Click "Create Support Ticket"
 * - Select category
 * - Staff responds
 * - Test auto-response (30 sec wait)
 * 
 * ‚úÖ Moderation:
 * - Send bad word ‚Üí Auto-delete + warning
 * - Spam messages ‚Üí Auto-timeout
 * - Staff: !ban @user <reason>
 * - Staff: !timeout @user <minutes> <reason>
 * 
 * ‚úÖ Beat Our Player:
 * - Staff: !beatplayer (create challenge)
 * - User with 10+ invites: Click button
 * - Staff: Setup match in ticket
 * 
 * ‚úÖ Leaderboards:
 * - Invite leaderboard (auto-updates)
 * - Tournament leaderboard: !leaderboard <game>
 * - Activity tracking
 * 
 * 
 * STEP 10: HOSTING OPTIONS
 * ------------------------
 * 
 * FREE OPTIONS:
 * 1. Replit.com
 *    - Upload code
 *    - Add secrets (env variables)
 *    - Click Run
 *    - Use UptimeRobot to keep alive
 * 
 * 2. Railway.app
 *    - Connect GitHub repo
 *    - Add environment variables
 *    - Auto-deploys
 * 
 * 3. Render.com
 *    - Connect repo
 *    - Add env variables
 *    - Free tier available
 * 
 * PAID OPTIONS:
 * 1. DigitalOcean ($5/month)
 * 2. AWS EC2
 * 3. Google Cloud
 * 4. Heroku
 * 
 * 
 * TROUBLESHOOTING
 * ---------------
 * 
 * ‚ùå Bot not responding:
 * - Check bot token in .env
 * - Verify bot is online in Discord
 * - Check all intents are enabled
 * - Verify bot has permissions
 * 
 * ‚ùå Commands not working:
 * - Check channel IDs are correct
 * - Verify bot can see channels
 * - Check role IDs
 * - Look at console for errors
 * 
 * ‚ùå Invites not tracking:
 * - Bot needs "Manage Server" permission
 * - Check invite cache initialization
 * 
 * ‚ùå DMs not working:
 * - User has DMs disabled
 * - Bot can't DM bots
 * - Check user privacy settings
 * 
 * ‚ùå Tournaments not posting:
 * - Verify channel IDs
 * - Check bot permissions (Send Messages, Embed Links)
 * - Look for errors in console
 * 
 * 
 * STAFF COMMANDS REFERENCE
 * ------------------------
 * 
 * TOURNAMENT MANAGEMENT:
 * !ct                          Create tournament (template)
 * !tournament <params>         Create custom tournament
 * !startroom <id> <room> <pw>  Start & send room details
 * !winners <id> @1 @2 @3       Declare winners
 * !endtournament <id>          End tournament
 * !tournaments                 List active tournaments
 * !leaderboard <game>          Show game leaderboard
 * !beatplayer                  Create beat player challenge
 * 
 * MODERATION:
 * !ban @user <reason>          Ban user
 * !timeout @user <min> <rsn>   Timeout user
 * !untimeout @user             Remove timeout
 * !warnings @user              Check warnings
 * !clearwarnings @user         Clear warnings
 * 
 * STAFF MANAGEMENT:
 * !addstaff @user              Add staff role
 * !removestaff @user           Remove staff role
 * 
 * UTILITY:
 * !announce <message>          Post announcement
 * !stats                       Show bot statistics
 * !syncprofiles                Sync profiles to channel
 * 
